# Change detection gates — consumed by scripts/ci/setup/ci-40-detect-changes.sh
#
# The script builds gates from TWO layers:
#
#   1. Auto-discovery (monorepo folder structure). Workspace roots are
#      scanned one level deep; every directory containing a metadata file
#      (graph-metadata.json, falling back to package.json) becomes a gate.
#      Dependencies between workspaces become graph edges automatically:
#        - graph-metadata.json: all keys of "dependencies"/"devDependencies"
#          plus the "runtimeDependencies" array (workspace names called over
#          HTTP/RPC at runtime — invisible to bundlers). The file is a
#          subset of package.json, so package.json can always be converted.
#        - package.json: only "workspace:*", "file:" and "link:" entries
#          plus the top-level "runtimeDependencies" array.
#   2. This rules file (user hardcoded values). Gates declared here are
#      merged on top of discovered ones: same name extends a discovered
#      gate with extra patterns/edges, new names add manual gates.
#
# Directives (reserved names, not gates):
#   discover: <root>/ [<root>/ ...]   workspace roots to scan
#                                     (default: packages/ apps/ services/ libs/ www/)
#                                     use "discover: none" to disable scanning
#   metadata: <file> [<file> ...]     metadata file priority per workspace
#                                     (default: graph-metadata.json package.json)
#
# Gate format (one per line):
#   <gate>: <pattern> [<pattern> ...] [@<ref> ...]
#
# - <gate> is the output name written to GITHUB_OUTPUT as <gate>=true|false.
#   Use letters, digits, underscores or dashes (prefer underscores: dashed
#   names need the outputs['my-gate'] syntax in workflow expressions).
#   Discovered gates are named after the workspace directory basename
#   (services/auth -> auth); on basename collisions the full path is used
#   (services_auth).
# - Patterns ending with "/" match every file under that directory prefix.
# - Other patterns are bash globs matched against the full repo-relative
#   path, where "*" crosses directory boundaries ("*.md" matches docs/a/b.md).
# - "@ref" adds a dependency edge (transitive closure): the gate fires when
#   any gate in its closure matches. A ref is resolved as a workspace
#   package name first ("@acme/auth"), then as a gate key ("@auth").
# - Lines starting with "#" and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Example for a monorepo where services depend on shared workspaces and on
# each other at runtime:
#   shared: packages/shared/
#   auth:   services/auth/ @shared
#   bff:    services/bff/ @auth @shared
#
# Gates below are for the CI Excellence repository itself (not a monorepo,
# so discovery finds nothing and these manual gates are the whole graph).

workflows: .github/
code: scripts/ config/ mise.toml .lefthook.toml @workflows
tests: spec/ @code
docs: docs/ *.md LICENSE
